{"id":12,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":12,"title":"Chapter 9: A New Home in the Promised Land","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 9"],["h1","A New Home in the Promised Land"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p3"},"The ship carrying Lehi’s family crossed the ocean and arrived at the promised land. The people set up their tents."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/18.23"},"1 Nephi 18:23"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p5"},"They prepared the soil and planted the seeds they had brought."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/18.24"},"1 Nephi 18:24"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p7"},"As they traveled around their new land, they found many kinds of animals. They also found gold, silver, and copper."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/18.25"},"1 Nephi 18:25"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p9"},"God told Nephi to make metal plates to write on. Nephi wrote about his family and their travels. He also wrote the words of God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/19.1,3"},"1 Nephi 19:1, 3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p11"},"Lehi grew old. Before he died he talked to his sons and told them to obey God’s commandments. He also blessed his grandchildren."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/1.14,16"},"2 Nephi 1:14, 16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/4.3-11"},"2 Nephi 4:3–11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p13"},"After Lehi died Laman and Lemuel became angry with Nephi and wanted to kill him. They did not want Nephi, their younger brother, to be their leader."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/4.13"},"2 Nephi 4:13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/5.2-3"},"2 Nephi 5:2–3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p15"},"The Lord told Nephi to lead the righteous people into the wilderness. They traveled for many days and finally stopped at a land they named Nephi."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/5.5-8"},"2 Nephi 5:5–8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p17"},"The people who followed Nephi obeyed God. They worked hard and were blessed. Nephi taught his people to build with wood and metal. They built a beautiful temple."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/5.10-11,15-16"},"2 Nephi 5:10–11, 15–16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p19"},"Laman and Lemuel’s followers called themselves Lamanites. They became a dark-skinned people. God cursed them because of their wickedness."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/5.14,21"},"2 Nephi 5:14, 21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p21"},"The Lamanites became lazy and would not work."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/5.24"},"2 Nephi 5:24"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_012_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p23"},"The people who followed Nephi called themselves Nephites. The Lamanites hated the Nephites and wanted to kill them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-9-a-new-home-in-the-promised-land.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/1.14"},"Jacob 1:14"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
